hopobject.body: I'm afraid that number's ex-directory healthyblenderrecipes.com/recipes/type/green_smoothies As compensation for terrorising their own people into submission, Arab regimes offered as meagre carrots jobs for life in their vast state bureaucracies, long a source of patronage and power. But the global recession, combined with the huge “youth bulge” that has left half of the Arab world’s population under 25, prevented the state from meeting its side of the bargain. An entire generation of young men, many of them college-educated, was growing up with little chance of a job, and therefore little chance of ever being marriage material in what is still a conservative society.
